  "text": "The RFS was developed by Kant et al [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and adapted by McCullough et al [CITATION_3] for our FFQ. The RFS focused on fruit, vegetables, whole grains, lean meats or meat alternates, and low-fat dairy products. Participants received 1 point for each recommended food consumed at least weekly. Based on the length of our FFQ, the maximum possible score was 51 (see Appendix A)",
